Author::::Ozjock
DateTime::::2016-03-08T10:47:05Z
There will always be gas flaring from rigs or platforms where oil or gas is being produced.In an emergency, or when a vessel or pipework becomes overpressured, the excess pressure from the gas has to be sent, via safety relief valves and pipework, to somewhere 'safe'. A cloud of gas suddenly venting to atmosphere would provide an explosive mixture that could ignite with devastating consequences, hence the need to burn it as it leaves the flare tower. A flame has to be continually maintained at the flare tower, usually from low pressure gas venting from other parts of the process.Most platforms use excess gas to power gas turbines and create their own electrical power. No need for the intermediate steam.



