Yes, Hydrogen works, but the problem is the efficency. You can't use electrolyses (sorry if spelled wrong, not native english speaker), because of the lacking efficency, if higher poweroutput is needed. Therfore you need to burn it, and since using electrolysis in large scale is not efficient (I think15-20), you are cooling the air, which uses also WAY to much energy (around 25-30% efficency). And since you are using again the process of buring the stuff, you get an overall efficiency of about 10-15%.



